ct chain (43.2-40=3.2, 3.2*10=32=2^sopfr) is operator-emitted, not auto-derived by the verifier. (7) **No new measurement performed** — pure hypothesis logging + cross-link to existing DD-5 + tecs-l-bridge.md docs. (8) **§5.1 partial answer** — answers WHAT 40 might decompose TO, not WHY 40 specifically vs 10/43 was chosen as anima implementation cardinality. (9) **R36 candidate tier** matches R34_CANDIDATE precedent (H-CX_candidate atlas-only, falsifiable test pre-registered). (10) **mac-local $0** — chflags unaffected (atlas + .roadmap unlocked per task brief assumption)."|"R36 candidate registration — DD-bridge DD-5 byproduct finding (Fisher I=43.2 exact for n=6, 43.2-40=3.2=2^sopfr(6)/10, 40 = tau*(sigma-phi)) permanently registered as candidate H-CX bridge between TECS-L information-theoretic capacity axis and ANIMA consciousness vector dimensional axis. Atlas witness ledger primary register (vs anima/.own = governance not empirical). Mirror pattern of R34_CANDIDATE (atlas-only candidate tier). Sister entry to R34 (coefficient axis) + R35 (governance scalar axis) — three orthogonal dimensions of same n=6 perfect-number arithmetic substrate. T1 internal-docs-conflict resolution required before promotion to R24-R32 confirmed tier."
