sult.json"]|["NP1: re-derive '0.608' from a documented authoritative source (consciousness_laws.json L837 references it as a string formula — locate the original fit data and method, NOT phi_scaling.py 5-point regression)","NP2: if NP1 fails to produce an N>=20 source for 0.608, deprecate the '0.608 = e^{-1/2}' hypothesis as untestable in current substrate inventory","NP3: T2/T3 (psi_balance perturbation, non-transformer substrate) DEFERRED until NP1 closes — meaningless to perturb a coefficient whose point estimate is unstable"]|"raw#10 honest — (1) T1 verdict is RETIRE_INCONCLUSIVE not RETIRE: the test executed cleanly but discriminative power is zero on both substrates. (2) The deeper finding is methodological: '0.608' as a documented constant is a string in consciousness_laws.json L837 + a 5-point regression that doesn't exactly reproduce 0.608 (got 0.425 / 0.553). (3) Original R34 registration honestly flagged 'C3_cross_substrate_corroboration NOT_MET — single fit datapoint Phi=0.608 from one model family' — T1 confirms this prerequisite gap is the binding constraint. (4) e^{-1/2} hypothesis is NOT falsified per se — it is unfalsifiable until 0.608 is re-anchored on N>=20 substrate. (5) A6.5 sum, ln(2), Law 2089 n/(s-phi) hypotheses ALL share this same prerequisite failure. (6) T1 RETIRE_INCONCLUSIVE preserves R34 ledger entry as 'tested, found prerequisite-weak' rather than promoting OR retiring on inadequate evidence."|["round 34 R34_CANDIDATE_phi_coefficient_e_minus_half (parent)","docs/discovery-algorithm-anima.md A6.5 (0.608 candidate decompositions)","ready/scripts/phi_scaling.py (the historic 5-point fit source — produces 0.425 not 0.608)","ready/core/consciousness_laws.json L837 ('phi_scaling: Phi = 0.608 x N^1.071' string declaration)","ready/core/consciousness_laws.json L3061 (Law 2089: 0.608 ≈ n/(sigma-phi) = 0.6 — Law 2089 hypothesis source)","ready/core/consciousness_laws.json L3818 (key_findings: 'Phi = 0.517*N - 1.27 (LINEAR, R²=0.9999)' — yet ANOTHER different fit on yet another substrate)"]|"R34 T1 execution complete with INCONCLUSIVE verdict — substrate-fragility revealed. R34_CANDIDATE retained in ledger, marked RETIRED_INCONCLUSIVE. No promotion to confirmed tier. T2/T3 deferred."
