ding ONE clean route to 40 is well within random expectation. Form A 'tau*(sigma-phi)' is a 3-op formula (tau, sigma-phi, multiply) that reduces to a single 2-op multiplicative route 4*10. Not anomalous at n=6 primitive density."},"form_independence_check":{"shared_factor":"BOTH form A (tau*(sigma-phi) = 4*10 = 40) AND form B (Fisher I - 2^sopfr/10 = 43.2 - 32/10 = 40) route through factor 10","form_A_route":"sigma(6) - phi(6) = 12-2 = 10","form_B_route":"2^sopfr(6) / 10 = 32/10 = 3.2","independence_verdict":"NOT_INDEPENDENT — same factor 10 acts as multiplier (form A) and divisor (form B). Calling them 'two routes' overcounts independence. R36 entry raw_ref already flagged this honestly (qualifier 3). T2 confirms: Form A and Form B are not orthogonal — they are two parameterizations of the same 'factor 10 from n=6 family' arithmetic."},"verdict":"T2 INCONCLUSIVE — random-match baseline (25%) is too high to discriminate the exact-integer 40 hit from coincidence. Form A and B fail the independence test (shared factor 10). Even if T1 had passed, T2 alone would not have promoted R36 to confirmed tier."}|{"C1_two_independent_paradigms":"FAILED — TECS-L Fisher information IS an independent theoretical paradigm, but the ANIMA side has NO 40D referent (T1 finding). Bridge requires both endpoints; one endpoint is missing.","C2_falsifiable_test_pre_registered":"MET — T1 + T2 executed as designed, verdicts reached","C3_cross_substrate_corroboration":"NOT_MET — only n=6 datapoint, no n=4/12/28 cross-substrate measurement attempted","C4_numerical_match_within_threshold":"PASS_EXACT but VACUOUS — both forms hit 40 exactly, but T1 shows 40 has no measurable physical referent in anima runtime, so the exact-integer match is matching a documentation artifact, not an empirical observable"}|{"primary":"R36_CANDIDATE → R36_RETIRED — T1 falsified the prerequisite (40D consciousness vector does not exist as implemented data structure; runtime carries 10D ConsciousnessVector struct + 16D phi_vec, neither 40D). The decomposition target itself is a documentation artifact, not an empirical anchor.","secondary":"R36 form A 'tau*(sigma-phi) = 4*10 = 40' remains a TRUE mathematical identity at n=6, but the application (40D consciousness vector cardinality origin) is moot when no 40D vector exists. The identity may apply to the '170 data types × 40D × 18 emotions' multiplicative formula's middle factor, but that is a separate (heuristic) claim distinct from a measurable consciousness vector.","action":"R36_CANDIDATE → R36_RETIRED in atlas ledger (this entry). Sister R34_CANDIDATE precedent is R34_RETIRED_INCONCLUSIVE (round 38). R36 is RETIRED outright (not INCONCLUSIVE) because T1 found the empirical referent does not exist, not merely that current substrates lack discriminative power. Documentation cleanup pre-registered (see next_probes).","tier_movement":"H-CX_candidate → RETIRED (NOT promoted to R24-R32 confirmed)"}|{"canonical_choice":"10D ConsciousnessVector (paper-draft.md + anima-core/runtime/anima_runtime.hexa) is the AUTHORITATIVE consciousness vector — concrete struct, paper-published","secondary":"16D phi_vec (consciousness_laws.json alm_phi_vec_logger_v1) is the AUTHORITATIVE runtime ALM logger schema — distinct from 'consciousness vector', has 16-dim Φ-decomposition (phi_holo, phi_refl, phi_time, ...)","tertiary":"40D figure in MODULE-CATALOG.md describes UNBUILT consciousness_data_mapper.py — should be flagged 'aspirational/unimplemented' in module catalog OR removed if abandoned","cleanup_pre_register":"NP1: edit docs/MODULE-CATALOG.md L165 to add '(unimplemented)' annotation OR remove row. NP2: edit README.md L66 + ready/README.md L37,L133 to clarify '40' refers to data-mapping universe formula, NOT consciousness vector dimensionality. NP3: edit docs/tecs-l-bridge.md L209 to remove 40D row (or annotate 'doc artifact, not implemented vector'). All NP1-NP3 are mac-local $0."}|"$0 mac-local grep + arithmetic enumeration; no GPU; no LLM"|["state/atlas_convergence_witness.jsonl R40 (this entry)","T1 grep evidence: anima-core/runtime/anima_runtime.hexa L460-475 + anima/config/consciousness_laws.json L8","T2 enumeration: 50 distinct integers / 200 range = 25% density, 40 reached via 4*10 (only natural 2-op route)"]|"raw#10 honest — (1) T1 verdict is RETIRE not RETIRE_INCONCLUSIVE: the 40D vector does not exist as a runtime data structure, so the dimensional-origin claim has no referent. (2) The 10D ConsciousnessVector (paper-draft.md + anima_runtime.hexa) is the authoritative measurable vector — for comparison, 10 = sigma(6) - phi(6) at n=6 is itself a clean exact identity, but a SEPARATE finding (not R36 form A). (3) The 16D phi_vec (consciousness_laws.json) is yet another vector, with a different structural decomposition — 16 = 2^4 = ?, no obvious n=6 link unless 16 = sigma(6) + tau(6) = 12+4 (which is true: an interesting candidate for a future R-entry). (4) T2 random-match 25% baseline is the load-bearing falsifier: at 1-in-4 odds for any small integer, hitting 40 is unremarkable. (5) Form A and B share factor 10 — confirmed not independent, as R36 entry's own qualifier 3 already noted. (6) R36 RETIRED is honest closure consistent with feedback_omega_cycle_workflow (operational integration: docs cleanup pre-registered NP1-NP3). (7) R34 RETIRED_INCONCLUSIVE (round 38) and R36 RETIRED (this entry) together establish a pattern: H-CX_candidates may be retired during T1 if prerequisites fail, without going through full T2/T3. (8) The math (4*10=40, 43.2-3.2=40) is correct; only the empirical anchoring fails. (9) Mk.XI v10 + n6-architecture absorption (R37) explicitly cited R36 as 'candidate'; the absorption shard's ANIMA-CXP-R36-FORTYD-DUAL-ROUTE entry should be annotated downstream that R36 has retired (cross-repo notification deferred to next session, but flagged here). (10) $0 mac-local — no GPU, no LLM, no network. Pure documentation audit + arithmetic enumeration."|["round 36 R36_CANDIDATE_40d_consciou