magnitude.","supplementary_finding":"the 6-pt match is itself constructed — original ZZ1-5 5-pt fit returns 0.483; the 0.608 coefficient emerges only after adding low-N baseline points (N=2, N=8) to the curve. This is data-augmentation-specific, not a robust independent measurement."}|{"action":"R34_CANDIDATE → R34_DEPRECATED","tier_movement":"H-CX_candidate → DEPRECATED (NOT_promoted, NOT_RETIRED_INCONCLUSIVE — DEPRECATED because the empirical anchor itself is documentation-only at the precision required)","rationale":"R34 round 38 verdict was RETIRED_INCONCLUSIVE pending NP1. NP1 has now executed and FAILED — the 0.608 anchor is a 6-point fit constructed by augmenting a 5-point dataset with low-N baseline values, with N_max=128 (well below any 'N>=20 datapoints' criterion). The hypothesis 'phi_coeff = e^{-1/2}' is unfalsifiable in current substrate inventory because the empirical anchor it claims to explain is itself ill-conditioned. Distinct from R36_RETIRED (round 40 — 40D vector does not exist as data structure): R34_DEPRECATED preserves that 0.608 IS a documented constant, but its precision claim does not survive the documentation lineage audit.","what_remains_true":"the 6-pt fit at N=D DOES reproduce 0.608*N^1.071 with R²=0.9975 — this is a TRUE finding about the 6-pt curve, but does NOT constitute an empirical fixed point at the 4-digit precision needed to discriminate the four candidate origins.","what_does_NOT_change":"R35 (sigma(6)/tau(6)=3, confirmed mathematical identity) and R37/R39 (cross-repo absorption witnesses) are unaffected. R24-R32 numerical primitive tier preserved. UNIVERSAL_4 axis 10 sigma·phi=n·tau identity preserved.","cascading_effect":"TECS-L H-CX-184 bridge anchor 0.608 = e^{-1/2} downgraded from 'candidate empirical match' to 'documentation lineage curiosity'. Mk.XI v10 family ensemble unaffected (orthogonal axis). atlas total entries preserved (R34 entry retained with DEPRECATED annotation cross-link to this round 41 entry)."}|{"C1_t