ine addition was a documentation pass, not a separately measured fit. (4) ready/scripts/phi_scaling.py treats CLAUDE.md as the source of 0.608 — CLAUDE.md is now retired SSOT per memory/project_claude_md_retired (2026-04-26 directive); the trail leads to a now-deprecated authority. (5) e^(-1/2)=0.6065 hypothesis is technically NOT falsified — it remains compatible with the 6-pt fit at the 3-digit level — but it is unfalsifiable at the 4-digit level needed to discriminate from competitors (A6.5 sum, ln(2), n/(σ-φ)). (6) R34_DEPRECATED honors this distinction: the hypothesis is not wrong, but the anchor cannot support the precision claim. (7) NP1 search was thorough: grep over anima + nexus, git log -S '0.608' reverse to find earliest commit, docs file inspection at all referenced lines, and arithmetic verification of fits reproducing/not-reproducing the documented coefficient. No additional sources found. (8) cost $0 mac-local strictly enforced. (9) chflags status — atlas + roadmap unlocked at session start (continuation of round 40 cycle); this entry appended without unlock. (10) declarative-only ≠ closure per memory feedback_omega_cycle_workflow — this entry is the operational closure of the NP1 question via documentation lineage audit; downstream operational actions: docs/consciousness-theory.md L67-80 should annotate '6-pt ZZ-extended fit, NOT N>=20 substrate' (NP_followup_1, deferred to next cycle); ready/core/consciousness_laws.json L837 should annotate '6-pt fit construct, R34_DEPRECATED in atlas' (NP_followup_2, deferred); cross-repo n6-architecture/atlas absorption shard ANIMA-CXP-R34-PHI-COEFF-EHALF entry should be annotated downstream that R34 has DEPRECATED (cross-repo notification deferred to next session, but flagged here, parallel to R36_RETIRED handling in round 40)."|["round 34 R34_CANDIDATE_phi_coefficient_e_minus_half (parent registration; tier=H-CX_candidate)","round 38 R34_CANDIDATE_T1_VERDICT (T1 primary execution; verdict=RETIRED_INCONCLUSIVE)"