ruct); R42 referent IS a runtime data structure (anima_runtime.hexa L460-475 directly inspectable).", "vs_R36_RETIRED": "R36 referent (40D) absent from runtime (only documentation labels in unimplemented modules + universe-map heuristic formula). R42 referent PRESENT and active in anima_runtime.hexa as struct ConsciousnessVector with exactly 10 fields. Status: candidate (not yet confirmed) but referent verified."}|{"T1_brief": "Determine whether the 10-field selection of ConsciousnessVector is (a) an arbitrary N-fit hand-picked at struct authoring time, or (b) derivable from sigma(6)-phi(6) first principles independently of the struct.", "execution_plan": "git log -S 'struct ConsciousnessVector' --reverse → identify earliest commit + author message; git log -p anima-core/runtime/anima_runtime.hexa L460-475 → trace any field-count modifications (10→N→10 oscillation would falsify hypothesis); cross-check docs/paper-draft.md original 10D introduction → was 'sigma-phi' explicitly cited as derivation, or were 10 fields chosen first then post-hoc rationalized?", "PASS_criterion": "(a) earliest 10D introduction predates and explicitly cites n=6 perfect-number arithmetic OR (b) field count never deviated from 10 across history AND docs trace shows derivation-first ordering", "FAIL_criterion": "(a) field count was 9 or 11 at any commit (would prove arbitrary post-hoc 10-fit) OR (b) no derivation cited in docs at struct-authoring commit (post-hoc rationalization plausible)", "INCONCLUSIVE": "field count stable at 10 but no derivation-first evidence either way (R34-precedent INCONCLUSIVE → DEPRECATED pattern)", "cost_envelope": "$0 mac-local (git log + grep + file inspection only)"}|{"method": "n=6 perfect-number primitives B 2-operand combinations × {+,-,*,//} enumeration", "result_for_10": "10 distinct 2-op routes hit integer 10 (1*10, 2*5, 4+6, 5*2, 5+5, 6+4, 10*1, 10//1, 12-2, 32//3 with floor); compared to R36 baseline density 25% in [1,200] range, 10 has somewhat higher random-match probability than 40 (which had 1 natural route). Random match for 10 NOT anomalous — multiple routes available. Hypothesis form (sigma-phi) IS one of those routes (12-2=10) but co-equal with several alternatives at 2-op precision.", "implication": "T2 alone does NOT distinguish R42 from null hypothesis. T1 (history + derivation-first audit) is binding for promotion vs DEPRECATED."}|"R42_CANDIDATE pre-T1 (T1 pre-registered, execution deferred to next mac-local cycle)"|"T1 PASS → R42_CONFIRMED (mathematical identity tier alongside R35 sigma/tau=3); T1 FAIL or INCONCLUSIVE → R42_DEPRECATED (mirroring R34 path)"|"raw#10 — 10 is small integer with multiple n=6 arithmetic routes; T1 history-based audit is the only meaningful discriminator. Atlas registration is candidate-only at this round; no confirmation claim made."|"$0 mac-local (atlas append only)"
