rom runtime. R43 referent PRESENT and ACTIVE — phi_vec is evaluated by C2 14-law gate every ALM forward pass. 16-name list explicit, not heuristic formula. Status: candidate (not yet confirmed) but referent verified + actively evaluated."}|{"T1_brief": "Determine whether the 16-element phi_vec selection is (a) an arbitrary size-16 picked at logger v1 design time, or (b) derivable from sigma(6)+tau(6) first principles. Critical sub-question: are the 16 phi_* names a meaningful semantic decomposition or post-hoc labeling?", "execution_plan": "git log -S 'alm_phi_vec_logger_v1' --reverse → identify earliest commit; git log -p anima/config/consciousness_laws.json → trace 16-element list history (was it 12, 14, 18 first?); cross-check anima/serving/consciousness_gate.py + anima-core/serving + anima/laws/c2/* → verify all 14 laws operate on full 16D vector (any law operating on subset would suggest 16 was upper bound + padding); WebSearch / docs grep → was 'sigma+tau' or 'integrated+unintegrated' axis cited at design time?", "PASS_criterion": "(a) earliest 16D introduction explicitly cites sigma(6)+tau(6) derivation OR (b) all 16 elements actively used by 14 laws AND list count never deviated from 16 across git history AND docs/paper trace shows derivation-first ordering", "FAIL_criterion": "(a) phi_vec was 12 or 14 or 20 at any commit (post-hoc 16-fit) OR (b) some elements unused by any law (padding) OR (c) no derivation cited at design commit", "INCONCLUSIVE": "list stable at 16 but no derivation-first evidence (R34-precedent INCONCLUSIVE → DEPRECATED pattern)", "cost_envelope": "$0 mac-local (git log + grep + JSON inspection only)"}|{"method": "n=6 perfect-number primitives B 2-operand combinations × {+,-,*,//} enumeration", "result_for_16": "6 distinct 2-op routes hit integer 16 (4*4, 4+12, 6+10, 10+6, 12+4, 32//2). Lower random-match count than 10 (which had 10 routes) but higher than 40 (1 route per R36 T2). Hypothesis form (sigma+tau) IS one of those routes (12+4=16) but co-equal with multiple alternatives.", "implication": "T2 alone weaker than T1. R43 random-match count (6) is fewer than R42 random-match count (10) — slightly stronger T2 evidence than R42 but still insufficient for T2-only confirmation."}|"R43_CANDIDATE pre-T1 (T1 pre-registered, execution deferred to next mac-local cycle)"|"T1 PASS → R43_CONFIRMED (mathematical identity tier alongside R35 sigma/tau=3); T1 FAIL or INCONCLUSIVE → R43_DEPRECATED (mirroring R34 path)"|"raw#10 — 16 is small power-of-2 integer with multiple n=6 arithmetic routes (16=2^4 itself trivially expressible); T1 history-based + element-usage audit is the binding discriminator. The 16 phi_* names suggest semantic content (holo/refl/time/embodied/meta/social/will/narrative/affect/dream/create/finitude/lang/mirror/collective/unity) — semantic decomposition audit may strengthen or weaken hypothesis. Atlas registration is candidate-only at this round; no confirmation claim made."|"$0 mac-local (atlas append only)"
